        "rich_text_KFEFt3": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Heading",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h1>The Portuguese Cut Diamond: History, Brilliance, and the Future of Sustainable Sparkle</h1>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "follow_us_3ggfwT": {
          "type": "follow_us",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Follow Us on"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_8DL9Df": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "1st Para",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Introduction: The Diamond That Outshines Them All</h2><p>Few diamonds capture light and legacy quite like the Portuguese Cut Diamond. Known for its deep brilliance and intricate faceting, this vintage cut combines history, artistry, and technical mastery in one exceptional gemstone. Its captivating symmetry and unparalleled sparkle make it a favorite among collectors and modern jewelry enthusiasts alike.</p><p>At Lucira Jewelry, we believe true luxury lies in the union of brilliance and responsibility. The Portuguese Cut Diamond embodies this balance perfectly — a radiant blend of timeless beauty and contemporary ethics through our innovative<a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/lab-grown-diamond-jewellery\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"> lab grown diamond jewellery</span></a> craftsmanship.</p>",
            "custom_id": "introduction"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_bUfHBT": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "What Is the Portuguese Cut Diamond?",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>What Is the Portuguese Cut Diamond?</h2>",
            "custom_id": "what"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_aKmq68": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/What_is_Portuguese_DIamond.jpg",
            "text": "<p>The Portuguese Diamond Cut is distinguished by its exceptional faceting, typically 161 to 200 facets compared to the 57 or 58 facets of most modern cuts. This intricate design maximizes light reflection, resulting in extraordinary fire and depth.</p><p>Unlike conventional diamond cuts that prioritize simplicity and uniformity, the Portuguese Cut celebrates complexity. Its high crown, small table, and deep pavilion create layers of light play, giving the diamond an almost three-dimensional glow. </p>",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_3i3W7r": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>This cut is a testament to the artistry of traditional gem cutting, where every facet is placed with intention to amplify the stone’s natural radiance.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_iyjamA": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "The History Behind the Portuguese Diamond Cut",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>The History Behind the Portuguese Diamond Cut</h2><p>The origins of the Portuguese Diamond Cut trace back to 18th-century Europe, where royal families and noble collectors sought the most brilliant diamonds available. Believed to have first emerged in Portugal’s historic gem-cutting houses, the cut soon became a symbol of prestige and sophistication.</p><p>As diamond design evolved, the Portuguese Cut became rarer, reserved for select stones that showcased perfect clarity and symmetry. Today, Lucira Jewelry reimagines this heritage through<a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/lab-grown-diamond-rings\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"> lab grown diamond rings</span></a>, preserving the legacy of craftsmanship while embracing sustainability and ethical sourcing.</p>",
            "custom_id": "history"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_Jc4E4r": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Anatomy of Brilliance: What Makes It So Special",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Anatomy of Brilliance: What Makes It So Special</h2><h3>Exceptional Faceting</h3>",
            "custom_id": "anatomy"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_WjJHra": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Exceptional_Facets_V2.jpg",
            "text": "<p>The Portuguese Cut features a unique concentric arrangement of facets that enhance its internal fire. With nearly three times the number of facets found in a standard cut, it produces a mesmerizing light performance.</p>",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "small"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_xAGLJV": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Depth and Dimension</h3><p>The deep pavilion and elevated crown allow light to travel through multiple planes, resulting in an unparalleled depth of sparkle.</p><h3>Elevated Crown and Smaller Table</h3><p>The smaller table emphasizes the diamond’s brilliance, while the raised crown provides a regal, domed effect — ideal for statement jewelry and heirloom pieces.</p><p>Each Portuguese Cut Diamond<a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/engagement-rings-for-women\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"> engagement ring for women</span></a> from Lucira is precisely crafted to highlight these defining characteristics, ensuring a rare balance of brilliance and elegance.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_6WCWXy": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Portuguese Cut Diamond vs Round Brilliant",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Portuguese Cut Diamond vs Round Brilliant</h2>",
            "custom_id": "comparison"
          }
        },
